Ninja Mountain Bike Performance | Laguna Mountains Camp
course:
Our camps are designed for the enthusiast rider or avid racer that is looking to build up and clean up their toolbox of mountain bike skills in order to handle a variety of terrain at speed.

We will blend an in-depth version of our traditional Intermediate  Advanced skills training with coached riding sessions and several mini-seminars on hot topics like nutrition, altitude acclimatization, and the perfect bike set-up.

After camp, you will see an immediate improvement in your riding and will have a boost in confidence on technical trails. You will be able to tackle rougher terrain and trickier corners with greater control and flow through single track, switchbacks, and berms with far more speed and efficiency.

Off the bike, you can enjoy all the scenery, shopping, and dining that your destination has to offer. Our camp locations are known as prime real estate not only for their awesome mountain bike trails, but also for their leisure activities. Any non-mountain bikers accompanying you for the long weekend will have more than enough to do to keep them happy and busy.

San Rafael Sunset Criterium
description:
Listen, this is criterium racing. 
This isnt waiting for two hours to see guys 
pass in 10 seconds. This isnt a TV commentator trying to add color to a grueling 8% grade climb through the Alps. This is What the heck was that? followed by $#!* Here they come again! And for that lethargic forty seconds the riders are out of sight on the backside of the course, American cyclings most renown voice and analyst, Dave Towle, is breaking down every nuance of whats happening before your eyes. And your blood is racing as 
local celebrity DJ Just pumps Afrojack and Pretty Lights through your veins... And you have a beer in your hand. And a cowbell in the other... This is a party. This is a nightclub on wheels, outdoors, under streetlights as dusk falls on an idyllic cityscape of Northern California in the summertime. This is one of the best annual events in all the 
Bay Area. You dont 
want to miss it. Racing Classes for Pro Men and Women, Masters  and new for this year, fixed gear racing categories.
course:
4-corner criterium .8-mile in downto
wn San Rafael, CA 8% grade incline 
leading into turn 3 and decline into turn 4 fun and fast. 
The course is 4th Street, D Street, 5th Street, A Street
notes:
All fields are limited and typically sell-out. Please register early. 

All participants will sign a waiver/release form at registration. Those under 18 require a parents signature. 

Bike Race is USA Cycling sanctioned. Riders must present a current USA Cycling license at registration. 1-day License  and Annual Licenses may be purchased on-site. 

Competitor age is determined by the age of the rider on Dec. 31st, 2017.

Fixed Gear races are open USA Cycling Category 1-5. Every rider must have a license, those without are able to purchase a 1-day license when registering or on site.

Held under USA Cycling Permit 
No refunds 
The event will be run rain or shine
directions: S/F is 4th and C Street, San Rafael CA. Racer parking in garage on 3rd and C Street or on surrounding city streets.

description: The Santa Monica Mountains tower above Malibu and the Pacific Coast like a jewel carved just for cyclists. Each day choose between an A or B Route for difficulty.
notes: This is not a race. It is a 5 day climbing cycling camp based out of the Santa Monica Mountains in Westlake Village, Ca.
